Text.Value: Kill that monster? You can't. It's impossible.
Tell me where he is, and I swear I'll end him.
I've done the impossible before.
Hurry. Please.
I can put this right, I swear. I'm here to stop the Black Mass - to kill Cazador.
He made me a spawn. Left me here to rot.
That scar on your face - it must bind you to Cazador's Black Mass.
One hundred and seventy years. You were one of my first too.
You called me so many sweet things. My name sounded like a lyric on your tongue.
You did this to me! You did this to us all! You cursed us to this hell.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Sebastian pointing at the player (Astarion) through the bars

Text.Value: You were my first. And my last.
You whispered my name, over and over. It sounded like a lyric on your tongue.
He called me darling, desire, delicious... but nothing sounded so sweet as the way he said Sebastian.
I damn you - damn you...
*You remember the taste of his lips, the heat of his body...*
That scar - Cazador did that to you? What does it mean?
The scar on your face - it must bind you to Cazador's Black Mass. I need to kill him.
*Approaching the cells, you're met by hollow faces and eyes reluctant to meet your gaze. There's an almost physical stink of decay and neglect.*
What are you doing? Stop - get out of my head!
You took them from me. You took everything from me!
His staff controls everything... If you can get it, maybe you can free us...
There were so many of you - I can't remember them all.
*But that is all.*
You smiled and joked and got me drunk.
I'm here to stop the Black Mass - to kill Cazador.
Sebastian.
Read his thoughts.
*Among the scars on his face is one you recognise - it's identical to one of the runes carved into your back.*
Maybe...
You should be dead. Why didn't Cazador feed on you?
Free? I'll never be free! I'll never be whole!
You're mistaken. I have no idea who you are.
I truly wanted you - Cazador forced me to harm you. I'll kill him.
*One of your conquests, claimed for Cazador. He should have been consumed long ago.*
You brought me to this hell. Abandoned me.
I remember you.
Tell me where he is, and I swear I'll end him.
But I can't rot - I can't die.
LIAR.
I damn you, Astarion! I damn you to the same misery you brought on us!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Sebastian pointing at the player (Astarion) through the bars
EditorData.NodeContext: Mix of rage and sobbing tears - Sebastian is broken

Text.Value: You're a monster.
You still make it sound so beautiful.
RAGH!

Text.Value: *He looks at you expectantly, his hollow eyes boring into yours.*
The grand chamber...
I can put this right, I swear. I can kill Cazador and free us all.
That scar - Cazador did that to you? He bound you to the Black Mass?
It's your fault. You stole my life - stole my death.
*Among the scars on his face is one is recognisable - identical to one of the runes carved into Astarion's back.*
I want to hear you say it again. Say my name.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: vampire spawn steps from the shadows at the rear of the cell into the light - he's emaciated, filthy, and dressed in rags that were once finery

Text.Value: I... I recognise that voice. You were in the Blushing Mermaid.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion steps closer to the cell

Text.Value: *The last time you heard this voice, it was singing drunkenly, whispering sweetly, then sighing with pleasure.*
Liar!
I'm so sorry.
Sebastian.
My family - my friends - they're gone...

EditorData.NodeContext: cracked voice, his mind is slipping

Text.Value: That scar on your face - what does it mean?
When he's dead, you'll be mine to command.
You. I know you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Prisoner at the back of the cell, in the shadows

Text.Value: Who are these wretches?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion walks toward the cells, looking at the prisoners through the bars
EditorData.NodeContext: Rhetorical question - not necessarily expecting an answer.

Text.Value: Well, at least you only had the best.
I can never forget you.
*And his name. Sebastian.*
You don't - you don't even remember...
I don't remember. I'm sorry.
I can fix this. When I kill Cazador, you'll be free.
No more games. Say my name!
How are you still alive?
His staff controls everything... If you can get it, maybe you can free us...
Try to remember his name.
How long has it been?

Synopsis: AOM/OOM dialog with the prisoners in Cazador's Palace. Astarion meets Sebastian - a young man he seduced and brought to Cazador - for the first time in 170 years. Astarion was sure Sebastian was dead, but Cazador secretly turned him into a vampire spawn. If you aggrevate Sebastian, he'll be so full of hate and pain that he'll curse you.
